Analysis of the Target Image  
────────────────────────────
• There are two separate “builds” in the scene:

1) Left “House‐like” Structure (6 total blocks, stacked in 5 levels):  
   – Bottom Layer: Two red arches side by side.  
   – Second Layer: One yellow rectangular block laid horizontally across those arches.  
   – Third Layer: A narrower red arch resting atop the yellow block.  
   – Fourth Layer: An orange rectangular block.  
   – Fifth (Top) Layer: An orange wedge forming the “roof.”  

2) Right “Tower & Frame” Structure (9 total blocks, stacked in 6 levels):  
   – Bottom: One green rectangular block (horizontal).  
   – Above It: One orange cylinder (vertical).  
   – Frame/Ring (four blocks): Two vertical green blocks (left/right) and two horizontal yellow blocks (top/bottom).  
   – Inside the Frame: One orange wedge, sitting on the cylinder.  
   – Above the Frame: One small horizontal green rectangular block.  
   – Very Top: One small blue rectangular block.  

Required Blocks From the Dictionary  
────────────────────────────────────
Below is one valid choice of dictionary blocks that match color, shape, and orientation exactly (duplicates allowed; no re‐orientation):

• Left Structure (6 blocks)  
  1) #1 (red arch) – left bottom arch  
  2) #1 (red arch) – right bottom arch  
  3) #10 (yellow rectangular, horizontal) – middle bridging block  
  4) #2 (red arch, narrower) – top arch  
  5) #12 (orange rectangular, vertical) – just below the roof  
  6) #15 (orange wedge) – roof piece  

• Right Structure (9 blocks)  
  7)  #9  (green rectangular, horizontal) – base  
  8)  #11 (orange cylinder, vertical) – column  
  9)  #10 (yellow rectangular, horizontal) – frame bottom bar  
  10) #8  (green rectangular, vertical) – frame left side  
  11) #8  (green rectangular, vertical) – frame right side  
  12) #10 (yellow rectangular, horizontal) – frame top bar  
  13) #14 (orange wedge) – inside the frame  
  14) #7  (green rectangular, horizontal) – block above frame  
  15) #5  (blue rectangular, horizontal) – topmost cube
